### GitHub Actions Workflow for Uploading Source Maps

Source: https://github.com/posthog/posthog.com/blob/master/contents/docs/error-tracking/upload-source-maps/github-actions.mdx

This YAML workflow configures a GitHub Actions job to build a Node.js project, inject source map metadata, and upload the source maps to PostHog. It requires checkout, Node.js setup, dependency installation, and a production build before executing the PostHog upload action. The action uses `directory`, `env-id`, and `cli-token` as essential inputs, with optional parameters for `project`, `version`, and `host`.

```yaml
name: Upload source maps to PostHog

on:
  push:
    branches: [main]

jobs:
  build_and_upload:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - uses: actions/setup-node@v4
        with:
          node-version: 20
          cache: npm
      - run: npm ci
      - run: npm run build

      # Inject and upload source maps using the PostHog action
      - name: Inject & upload source maps to PostHog
        uses: PostHog/upload-source-maps@v0.4.6
        with:
          directory: dist
          env-id: ${{ secrets.POSTHOG_ENV_ID }}
          cli-token: ${{ secrets.POSTHOG_CLI_TOKEN }}
          # host: https://eu.posthog.com # Required only for EU cloud
          # project: my-awesome-project  # Optional; falls back to repo name
          # version: ${{ github.sha }}   # Optional; falls back to current commit SHA
```

